\cf0 What physics can explain these missing spectrum chunks? In short it\'92s because of the absorption of photons by gases in the atmosphere. Let\'92s look at specifically how this happens, starting with individual atoms. We\'92ll use the element Helium in particular. Like all atoms Helium is composed of a nucleus and electrons that orbit the nucleus and it looks something like this:\
\
